The paper focuses on measuring the performance of public research institutions in collaboration with the domestic industry, which involves analyzing co-authorship of scientific publications. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), and sound (cs.SD).
